209
00:16:05,174 --> 00:16:08,427
Do you mind if I look
over it for a bit?

210
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:09,678
Oh, sure. Sure.

211
00:16:11,513 --> 00:16:14,099
[Larry breathing deeply]

212
00:16:20,522 --> 00:16:22,149
Mmm… [sighs]

213
00:16:32,701 --> 00:16:36,371
Uh, this is consent
for the polygraph.

214
00:16:36,455 --> 00:16:37,956
I ca... I can't take that.

215
00:16:39,875 --> 00:16:41,126
Why not?

216
00:16:42,002 --> 00:16:43,795
Because I don't
believe I'll pass.

217
00:16:44,296 --> 00:16:46,381
[whistles]

218
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:49,885
[Mark] Mmm, why
do you think that?

219
00:16:54,264 --> 00:16:55,682
- [door opens]
- It would...

220
00:16:59,394 --> 00:17:01,396
- Here you go.
- [Larry] Thank you.

221
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,689
[Brian clears throat]

222
00:17:04,942 --> 00:17:06,193
Could you just do...

223
00:17:06,276 --> 00:17:09,445
Would you mind leaving? I ju...
Your energy makes me feel itchy.

224
00:17:12,199 --> 00:17:13,325
Sure thing, Larry.

225
00:17:24,336 --> 00:17:25,546
[sighs]

226
00:17:26,547 --> 00:17:29,591
[Larry] You know, I am sorry.
I'm just so tired right now.

227
00:17:30,592 --> 00:17:32,010
I'm afraid to sleep.

228
00:17:32,094 --> 00:17:34,096
[stutters] I have
nightmares all the time,

229
00:17:34,179 --> 00:17:38,100
and I… and I get
depressed, like, bad.

230
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,602
[Mark] Have you seen
anyone about that?

231
00:17:41,103 --> 00:17:44,565
Yeah, I went to a
counselor once, but it...

232
00:17:44,648 --> 00:17:45,858
He was young.

233
00:17:46,441 --> 00:17:48,151
And he wasn't very helpful.

234
00:17:48,235 --> 00:17:49,236
Yeah.

235
00:17:51,113 --> 00:17:55,492
Well, uh, besides the nightmares,
what else depresses you?

236
00:17:56,785 --> 00:17:58,829
I'm... I'm very lonely.

237
00:18:00,205 --> 00:18:01,206
That's hard.

238
00:18:02,207 --> 00:18:04,626
Yeah, it is hard. Like,
I wa... I wake up alone.

239
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:07,629
I g-go to work alone.
I go to bed alone.

240
00:18:10,340 --> 00:18:13,385
Some other guys,
they have women.

241
00:18:13,468 --> 00:18:17,097
They go to movies. They
eat pizza together.

242
00:18:17,598 --> 00:18:20,684
And you wish you had that?
A woman who loved you.

243
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:24,062
[breathes shakily] Yes.

244
00:18:24,563 --> 00:18:27,608
But you don't feel that's possible?
You don't think women like you?

245
00:18:30,235 --> 00:18:32,404
N-No. No.

246
00:18:32,487 --> 00:18:33,655
So… [sighs]

247
00:18:33,739 --> 00:18:38,202
Wh-what do you do with the
urge… to be with a woman?

248
00:18:40,245 --> 00:18:41,663
Always push it down.

249
00:18:42,164 --> 00:18:43,373
It's gotta be hard.

250
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:47,878
And it's probably what
causes the nightmares.

251
00:18:47,961 --> 00:18:51,006
You know, you push it down, it climbs
right back up into your dreams.

252
00:18:51,089 --> 00:18:54,760
Yeah, th-that's why I do such awful
things in my nightmares, it...

253
00:18:54,843 --> 00:18:57,888
That's all that they are, though.
It's just dreams, you know.

254
00:19:03,894 --> 00:19:07,314
She wasn't in your dreams,
Larry. She was in your reality.

255
00:19:08,649 --> 00:19:12,236
I thou... I thought she
was. I thought she was.

256
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:13,820
No.

257
00:19:17,407 --> 00:19:18,867
Can I touch her?

258
00:19:21,578 --> 00:19:22,579
[Mark] Sure.

259
00:19:30,879 --> 00:19:32,381
Tell me how you met her.

260
00:19:36,885 --> 00:19:38,512
She was riding her bike,

261
00:19:38,595 --> 00:19:42,015
and, uh, I drove up and
I stopped to talk to her.

262
00:19:42,683 --> 00:19:46,436
She was so very nice, you
know. Very nice at first.

263
00:19:46,979 --> 00:19:48,146
[Mark] And then she wasn't?

264
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:49,510
[Larry] No, she was always nice.

265
00:19:49,565 --> 00:19:53,235
It's just that she...
She got sad, real sad.

